net.njcull.collections

Class Collectors

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.njcull.collections.Collectors

  • public final class Collectors
extends java.lang.Object
    Implementations of stream Collectors for the maps and sets in this package. Variations include map versus bimap, and various sorting options for those sets and maps that are ordered.
    Version:
    9/01/2016.

      • toImmutableArrayBiMap

        public static <K,V> java.util.stream.Collector<java.util.Map.Entry<? extends K,? extends V>,?,ImmutableArrayMap<K,V>> toImmutableArrayBiMap()
        Returns a Collector that accumulates the input elements into a new ImmutableArrayMap, created as a bimap, in encounter order.

        A bimap is a map where both keys and values are unique. Any given key can be mapped "forwards" to a single value; any given value can be mapped "backwards" to a single key.

        Type Parameters:
        K - the type of keys in the resulting map
        V - the type of values in the resulting map
        Returns:
        a Collector which collects all the input keys and values into a ImmutableArrayMap, created as a bimap, in encounter order
